ed by carers due to the COVID-19 pandemic</span></h3></div></div></div></div></div><button aria-label="Previous" class="glider-prev glider-nav glider-nav-1"></button><button aria-label="Next" class="glider-next glider-nav glider-nav-1"></button><div class="glider-dots glider-d-1"></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-22_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-23_"><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-24_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-26_">This week is Carer’s Awareness Week (7-13th June 2021) with the theme “Make Caring Visible and Valued”. The plight of community care workers has been highlighted throughout the COVID-19 pandemic. For example, did you know that:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-oeezt OJJCp pf-27_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-28_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-30_">1 in 8 adults (around 6.5 million people) are carers</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-31_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-33_">Every day another 6,000 people take on a caring responsibility – that equals over 2 million people each year.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-34_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-36_">58% of carers are women, and 42% are men.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-37_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-39_">1.3 million people provide over 50 hours of care per week.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-40_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-42_">Over 1 million people care for more than one person.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-43_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-45_">As of 2020, Carers UK estimates around 13.6 million people are caring through the pandemic.</span></li></ul><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-46_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-48_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" id="about" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-49_"><div class="sc-iNiQyp jdiWPe"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-50_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-51_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:5"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-52_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-53_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-54_"><div data-pf-type="Block" class="sc-Arkif eJDRKz pf-55_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-56_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-58_">Who is a carer?</span></h3></div></div></div></div><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-59_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-61_">A carer is anyone, including adults and children, who looks after a family member, friend, or partner who requires help because of their frailty, illness, disability, mental health problem, or addiction. They may not be able to cope without their support. <br><br>
It can be challenging for carers to see their caring role as separate from their relationship with the person they care for, whether that relationship is as a parent, child, sibling, partner, or friend.
<br><br>This means that the sort of roles and responsibilities that carers have to provide varies widely.
</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-62_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-64_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" id="details" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-65_"><div class="sc-iNiQyp jdiWPe"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-66_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-67_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-68_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-69_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-70_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-72_">What do carers do</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-73_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-75_">The roles and responsibilities of carers vary as much as the people they support. The duties of a carer can include:<br><br></span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-oeezt OJJCp pf-76_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-77_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-79_">Practical tasks such as tidying the house, doing the washing, ironing, paying the bills, cooking meals, shopping.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-80_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-82_">Personal care including, dressing, washing, repositioning, giving medication or collecting prescriptions, and attending doctors’ appointments.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-83_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-85_">Emotional support such as providing a listening ear, offering help and advice, giving reassurance and befriending.</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-86_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-88_">Everyday tasks such as getting out of bed and personal care, such as bathing, to emotional support, such as helping someone cope with the symptoms of a mental illness.</span></li></ul><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-89_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-91_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-92_"></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-93_"><div class="sc-iNiQyp jdiWPe"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-94_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-95_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-96_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-97_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-98_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-99_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-101_">What is the impact of COVID-19 on carers’ well-being?</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-102_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-104_">The current and residual impacts of COVID-19 on unpaid carers include their economic, physical and psychological well-being. While carers weren’t alone in experiencing 2020 as a highly emotional and unstable period, they faced unique pressures, demands and time commitments often overlooked by society.
<br><br>They must now navigate fast-changing care delivery models, provide emotional support despite their own emotional needs, and handle increased responsibilities at home - all at once. Amid these rising responsibilities, many carers sacrifice their health and well-being for the sake of the people they love. They also deal with emotional isolation.<br>
<br>Financial strife hits hard as unemployment spikes and salaries are imperilled. Many carers lack the time to care for their physical and emotional health. There are even more nuanced challenges when looking at women carers, younger, middle-aged and older carers, who encounter increasing inequities. In taking a hard look at how the pandemic has affected the globe, carers have faced unprecedented challenges – they are undercounted, unheard and struggling. More than ever, governments, public entities, the private sector, and all citizens have roles in addressing that problem.
</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-105_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-107_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-108_"><div class="sc-iNiQyp jdiWPe"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-109_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-110_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-111_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-112_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-113_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-115_">What is the impact on carers’ mental health?</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-116_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-118_">Cares continued to fare worse than non-carers regarding mental health and fatigue, and long-term carers were more likely to report symptoms such as headache, body aches, and abdominal discomfort.<br><br>The nature of caregiving differed between short-term and long-term carers, with the latter more likely to provide more significant hours of care and to be looking after patients with permanent medical conditions. Efforts to understand and mitigate the impact of the pandemic on population health should include carers whose mental and physical health were already vulnerable before COVID-19.</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-119_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-121_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-122_"></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-123_"><div class="sc-iNiQyp jdiWPe"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-124_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-125_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:5"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-126_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-127_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-129_">Challenges faced by carers</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-130_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-132_">The role of a carer can be very challenging. Unfortunately, many assume this role unprepared and may not have a real choice when they become a carer. This may be due to their legal or moral obligation to provide care, the lack of formal, alternative care arrangements, or simply because information about such alternatives is missing.</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-133_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-135_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-136_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-137_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-138_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-139_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-141_">Key challenges of caregiving</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-142_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-144_">While being a carer can be a genuinely rewarding experience, the caregivers often face common challenges that leave them overwhelmed, anxious and/or intimidated by their duties. Some of these challenges a family caregiver faces are:</span></p><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-oeezt OJJCp pf-145_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-146_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-148_">Managing their time.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-149_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-151_">Emotional and physical stress.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-152_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-154_">Lack of privacy.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-155_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-157_">Financial strain.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-158_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-160_">Sleep deprivation.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-161_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-163_">Being afraid to ask for help.&nbsp;</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-164_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-166_">Depression and isolation.&nbsp;</span></li></ul></div></div></div><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-167_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-169_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:3;--c-sm:2;--c-md:1;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-170_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-171_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:5"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-172_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-173_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-174_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-175_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-177_">Financial costs for carers</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-178_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-180_">There are also high hidden costs for carers. These include the opportunity costs of lost earnings, careers and pension entitlements, and the health consequences of the physical and psychological burden experienced. Without adequate support, it can put carers at risk of poverty, ill-health and social isolation.</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-181_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-183_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-184_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-185_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-186_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-187_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-189_">Lack of visibility</span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-190_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-192_">In 2017, COFACE Families Europe consulted over 1000 family carers across 16 countries about the challenges they faced. The extent to which carers are affected by these challenges depends on the care regime in which they live, on the stage of life during which they become an informal carer. On the options and choices, they have in their given context.&nbsp;<br><br>Overall, the recognition of carers' work and its value is very low, both by society, their families and immediate circles. Although they fill significant gaps in formal long-term care provision, carers are rarely considered as co-producers of social services, despite their developing a wide range of skills and being experts by experience. The voice and representation of informal carers should be strengthened to raise awareness of the problems linked to the caring role.</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-193_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-195_">Click here to register</span></a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-196_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-197_"></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-198_"><div class="sc-dlMDgC kpPvTx pf-199_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-200_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-ezzafa qUTLf pf-201_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-203_">Support available for carers<br></span></h3><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-204_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-206_">If you are a carer who needs assistance, you can reach out to Carers UK helpline on 0808 808 7777 from Monday to Friday, 9 am – 6 pm, or contact them by email (<a href="/mailto:advice@carersuk.org" target="_blank">advice@carersuk.org</a>). They provide information and guidance to unpaid carers, covering a range of subjects, including:</span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-hTRkXV enlJuL pf-207_"><ul style="--text-indent:0;--line-spacing:10px" data-pf-type="List" class="sc-oeezt OJJCp pf-208_"><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-209_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-211_">Benefits and financial support</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-212_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-214_">Your rights as a carer in the workplace</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-215_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-217_">Carers' assessments and how to get help in your caring role</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-218_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-220_">Services available to carers and the people you care for</span></li><li data-pf-type="List.Item" class="sc-hhIiOg iwisNA pf-221_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-223_">How to complain effectively and challenge decisions</span></li></ul><p class="sc-lbVvki flSuVc pf-224_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-226_">You can also join a <a href="https://www.carersuk.org/forum" target="_blank" style="">Carers' Forum</a>, an online community of carers and Carers UK members 24 hours a day, 365 days a year. A few words from a fellow carer who understands what you're going through can be a lifeline.&nbsp;</span></p><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/free-coping-with-stress-at-work-elearning-course" target="_blank" data-pf-type="Button" class="sc-kfYoZR ccMiJj pf-227_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jUfyBS eSyZIh pf-229_">Click here to register</spa